text:
Hi

I've very new to the log4j package but it seems realy to be a good log package,
thanks a lot. The version I use is 1.1.3.
I've implemented my own Categeory and have noticed some minor performance
problems in the class Category.

The method
  public
  void debug(Object message) {
    if(hierarchy.disable >=  Priority.DEBUG_INT) 
      return;    
    if(Priority.DEBUG.isGreaterOrEqual(this.getChainedPriority())) {
      forcedLog(FQCN, Priority.DEBUG, message, null);
    }
  }

is fine designed but debug(Object message, Throwable t) or

  public
  void error(Object message) {
    if(hierarchy.disable >=  Priority.ERROR_INT) return;
    if(this.isEnabledFor(Priority.ERROR))
      forcedLog(FQCN, Priority.ERROR, message, null);
  }

has the same check twice (hierarchy.disable >= ...), one in the method and one 
time
in the method isEnabledFor(). I think you should ONLY use isEnabledFor for both
checks or if performance stuff is the idea do the own checks like in 
debug(Object message).
Not it's a mix of both.
Of course there are more methods in the same package with the same 'problem'.


Greetings

Beat
